  "description": [
    "jxj J k BP1 jVf The Minot fire department is run more economically than any other fire department in a city the size of Minot in the United States the Independent ventures to state There are only four salaried men in the department The chief W R Leas draws 15000 a month The salary of the assistant chief J J OLeary is 14000 The two drivers F T Hunsley and H M Miller re ceive 125 a month each These men are on duty 36 out of every 48 hours and even during the 12 hours they are off duty they must be within call There are 23 volunteer firemen tho usually 12 of them respond to each call In case of a second alarm practically all of them turn out Four of the volunteer firemen sleep at the hall tho they hold other positions in the city All are provided with suits tho unless they are at home when the call is given they respond in what ever clothing they happen to be wear ing at the time In a recent fire a volunteer fireman ruined a 20 silk shirt He received 300 for the work that night The"
  ],
